description:
Test files extensively mock `window.scribe` API but use 'any' types throughout:

**Pattern in 80+ test locations:**
```typescript
(window as any).scribe = {
  notes: { list: vi.fn(), ... },
  search: { query: vi.fn(), ... },
  // etc
}
```

**Solution:**
Create a proper type declaration:

1. Create `apps/desktop/renderer/src/types/scribe.d.ts`:
```typescript
interface ScribeAPI {
  notes: {
    list(): Promise<Note[]>;
    read(id: NoteId): Promise<Note>;
    create(note: Partial<Note>): Promise<Note>;
    save(note: Note): Promise<void>;
    delete(id: NoteId): Promise<void>;
    // ... other methods
  };
  search: {
    query(text: string): Promise<SearchResult[]>;
  };
  // ... other namespaces
}

declare global {
  interface Window {
    scribe: ScribeAPI;
  }
}
```

2. Update tests to use typed mocks:
```typescript
window.scribe = {
  notes: { list: vi.fn<[], Promise<Note[]>>(), ... },
};
```

**Impact:** Eliminates ~80 'any' usages in tests, improves test type safety

