## Overview

Implement the `extractRelevantExcerpt()` utility for query-aware excerpt extraction with multiple strategies.

## API

```typescript
interface ExcerptConfig {
  strategy: 'full' | 'heading-bounded' | 'sentence-window' | 'summary';
  tokenBudget: number;
  minContextSentences: number;  // Sentences before/after match (default: 2)
}

function extractRelevantExcerpt(
  note: Note,
  query: string,
  config: ExcerptConfig
): { excerpt: string; tokens: number };
```

## Strategy Options

| Strategy | Description | Use Case |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `full` | Include entire note content | Small notes, high relevance |
| `heading-bounded` | Extract sections containing query terms | Structured notes with clear headings |
| `sentence-window` | Extract sentences around query matches | Dense prose without clear structure |
| `summary` | First paragraph + query-matching sections | Long notes with token budget constraints |

## Default Algorithm: Heading-Bounded with Fallback

```typescript
function extractRelevantExcerpt(
  note: Note,
  query: string,
  config: ExcerptConfig
): { excerpt: string; tokens: number } {
  const fullText = extractTextFromNodes(note.content.root.children);
  const fullTokens = estimateTokens(fullText);

  // If note fits in budget, return full content
  if (fullTokens <= config.tokenBudget) {
    return { excerpt: fullText, tokens: fullTokens };
  }

  // Extract headings to find section boundaries
  const headings = extractHeadings(note.content);
  const queryTerms = tokenizeQuery(query);

  // Score each section by query term density
  const sections = segmentByHeadings(note.content, headings);
  const scoredSections = sections.map(section => ({
    ...section,
    score: computeTermDensity(section.text, queryTerms),
    tokens: estimateTokens(section.text)
  }));

  // Greedy selection: highest scoring sections within budget
  scoredSections.sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score);

  const selected: typeof scoredSections = [];
  let usedTokens = 0;

  for (const section of scoredSections) {
    if (usedTokens + section.tokens <= config.tokenBudget) {
      selected.push(section);
      usedTokens += section.tokens;
    }
  }

  // Re-sort by document order for coherent reading
  selected.sort((a, b) => a.startOffset - b.startOffset);

  // Join with ellipsis markers between non-adjacent sections
  const excerpt = selected
    .map((s, i) => {
      const prev = selected[i - 1];
      const needsEllipsis = prev && s.startOffset > prev.endOffset + 1;
      return (needsEllipsis ? '\n...\n\n' : '') + s.text;
    })
    .join('');

  return { excerpt, tokens: usedTokens };
}
```

## Term Density Scoring

```typescript
function computeTermDensity(text: string, queryTerms: string[]): number {
  const words = text.toLowerCase().split(/\s+/);
  const termSet = new Set(queryTerms.map(t => t.toLowerCase()));

  let matches = 0;
  for (const word of words) {
    if (termSet.has(word)) matches++;
    // Partial match bonus for prefix matching
    for (const term of termSet) {
      if (word.startsWith(term) && word !== term) matches += 0.5;
    }
  }

  // Normalize by section length to avoid bias toward long sections
  return matches / Math.sqrt(words.length);
}
```

## Fallback Chain

1. Try heading-bounded strategy
2. Fall back to sentence-window if no headings found
3. Fall back to first N tokens if no query matches

