## Overview

Create the EngineLoader class that manages lazy initialization of FileSystemVault, SearchEngine, GraphEngine, and TaskIndex.

## Implementation Details

### index/loader.ts
```typescript
class EngineLoader {
  private searchEngine?: SearchEngine;
  private graphEngine?: GraphEngine;
  private vault?: FileSystemVault;
  private taskIndex?: TaskIndex;
  private loaded = false;

  constructor(private vaultPath: string) {}

  async ensureLoaded(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.loaded) return;

    this.vault = new FileSystemVault(this.vaultPath);
    await this.vault.load();  // Only async operation - reads files from disk
    this.loaded = true;
  }

  async getVault(): Promise<FileSystemVault> {
    await this.ensureLoaded();
    return this.vault!;
  }

  async getSearchEngine(): Promise<SearchEngine> {
    await this.ensureLoaded();

    if (!this.searchEngine) {
      this.searchEngine = new SearchEngine();  // Sync constructor
      const notes = this.vault!.list();
      for (const note of notes) {
        this.searchEngine.indexNote(note);
      }
    }
    return this.searchEngine;
  }

  async getGraphEngine(): Promise<GraphEngine> {
    await this.ensureLoaded();

    if (!this.graphEngine) {
      this.graphEngine = new GraphEngine();  // Sync constructor
      const notes = this.vault!.list();
      for (const note of notes) {
        this.graphEngine.addNote(note);
      }
    }
    return this.graphEngine;
  }

  async getTaskIndex(): Promise<TaskIndex> {
    await this.ensureLoaded();

    if (!this.taskIndex) {
      // Direct import required for Node.js/Bun contexts
      const { TaskIndex } = await import('@scribe/engine-core/src/task-index.js');
      const { JsonlTaskPersistence } = await import('@scribe/engine-core/src/task-persistence.js');

      const persistPath = path.join(this.vaultPath, '.scribe', 'tasks.jsonl');
      const persistence = new JsonlTaskPersistence(persistPath);
      this.taskIndex = new TaskIndex(persistence);
      await this.taskIndex.load();

      // Index all notes
      const notes = this.vault!.list();
      for (const note of notes) {
        this.taskIndex.indexNote(note);
      }
    }
    return this.taskIndex;
  }
}
```

## Key Design Decisions

1. **Lazy initialization**: Only load engines when first requested
2. **Sync constructors**: SearchEngine and GraphEngine have sync constructors, only FileSystemVault.load() is async
3. **TaskIndex direct import**: Must import from internal path to avoid browser bundle issues
4. **Caching**: Once an engine is loaded, it's cached for the session

## Exit Criteria

- EngineLoader can load vault and index notes
- Each engine getter only initializes on first call
- TaskIndex imports from internal path without errors
- Unit tests verify lazy loading behavior

