## Overview

Implement the `vault retrieve` command with multi-signal ranking combining keywords, title match, tags, recency, and link density.

## Command Specification

```bash
vault retrieve --query "authentication design" --k 10 --json
vault retrieve -q "onboarding" --boost-recent --json
```

### Options
| Flag | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `--query, -q` | string | required | Query text |
| `--k` | number | 20 | Top-k results |
| `--boost-recent` | boolean | false | Weight recent edits higher |
| `--boost-linked` | boolean | false | Weight highly-linked notes higher |
| `--tags` | string | - | Required tags (comma-separated) |
| `--exclude-tags` | string | - | Excluded tags |
| `--type` | string | - | Note type filter |
| `--json` | boolean | false | JSON output |

### Scoring Formula
```
score = (0.4 * text_match) 
      + (0.25 * title_match) 
      + (0.15 * tag_match) 
      + (0.10 * recency_decay) 
      + (0.10 * link_centrality)
```

